COMMENDATIONS: Commends Robert E. Smith Lupo for his service to Lakeview and
the city of New Orleans
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Robert E. "Bob" Smith Lupo for his service to Lakeview and the city of New
3 Orleans.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Robert E. "Bob" Smith Lupo for his
5 professional achievements and to commend him for his service to the Lakeview
6 neighborhood and the city of New Orleans; and
7 WHEREAS, Robert E. "Bob" Smith Lupo began his career at the age of fourteen
8 working as a laborer unloading railroad boxcars; he then served as a junior executive with
9 the Southern Railway System, and after a few years, became a salesman for the New Orleans
10 Land Company; and
11 WHEREAS, Bob formed a real estate development organization with his wife,
12 Hettie; he developed single-family homes, designed by his wife, in the Lakeview
13 neighborhood and ultimately branched out into commercial development; and
14 WHEREAS, following Hurricane Katrina, Bob took on the significant task of
15 restoring his commercial properties; through this work, he helped stabilize local commerce
16 and contributed to the revitalization of many neighborhoods; and
17 WHEREAS, Bob's generosity and support of public institutions strengthened the
18 foundations of the Lakeview community; he made valuable contributions to the Lakeview
19 library, which bears his name, and the New Orleans Fire Department's historic Engine 18
20 Firehouse; and
